---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const basePath = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const brandLogoHref = `${basePath}brand/startline-sites-primary-horizontal.svg`;
---
<Base>
  <nav id="nav">
    <a href="#top" class="brand" aria-label="StartLine Sites home"><img class="brand-mark" src={brandLogoHref} alt="StartLine Sites" width="1200" height="360" /></a>
    <div class="nav-links" id="navLinks">
      <a href="#problem">Why us</a><a href="#templates">Templates</a><a href="#how">How it works</a><a href="#pricing">Pricing</a><a href="#faq">FAQ</a><button class="btn btn-accent" data-scroll="audit">Private race website audit</button>
    </div>
    <button class="hamburger" id="burger" aria-label="Menu" aria-controls="navLinks" aria-expanded="false"><span></span><span></span><span></span></button>
  </nav>
  <main id="main">
    <section class="hero" id="top"><div class="hero-inner"><div class="hero-text reveal"><span class="eyebrow">From the team behind BMQR</span><h1>Race websites built to turn <span class="ital">interest</span> into registrations.</h1><p class="lead">StartLine Sites builds fast, SEO-optimized websites for race directors — designed to help runners find your race, trust the details, and click through to register.</p><div class="hero-cta"><button class="btn btn-accent" data-scroll="audit">Request a private race website audit →</button><button class="btn btn-ghost" data-scroll="templates">See the templates</button></div><div class="trust"><div class="dots"><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span><span class="dot"></span></div><span>Built for search, speed, and signups.</span></div></div><div class="reveal"><div class="demo-wrap"><div class="demo-browser"><div class="bw-bar"><span class="bd"></span><span class="bd"></span><span class="bd"></span><span class="url">oceanmarathon.com</span></div><div class="bw-content"><svg class="bw-mountains" viewBox="0 0 600 120" preserveAspectRatio="none"><path d="M0 120 L0 70 L100 30 L200 65 L320 25 L450 60 L550 30 L600 55 L600 120Z" fill="#0B0E13" opacity=".95"/></svg><div class="bw-hero-text"><div class="e">● September 20, 2026 · Oregon</div><div class="demo-title">Ocean<br/>Marathon</div><div class="sub">The marathon that follows the coast.</div><div class="cd"><div class="cd-u">112<small>Days</small></div><div class="cd-u">14<small>Hrs</small></div><div class="cd-u">22<small>Min</small></div></div></div></div></div><div class="lh-badge"><div class="ring"><svg viewBox="0 0 60 60"><circle class="bg" cx="30" cy="30" r="26"/><circle class="fg" cx="30" cy="30" r="26"/></svg><span class="score">98</span></div><div class="label"><b>Lighthouse Score</b>Performance · SEO · A11y</div></div></div></div></div></section>
    <section class="problem" id="problem"><div class="section-head reveal"><div><div class="kicker">The problem</div><h2>Three reasons runner interest never becomes registrations.</h2></div><p class="lead">Most race websites are either an aging WordPress site nobody's touched in years, or a registration platform listing pretending to be a homepage. Either way, interested runners leave before they trust the details and click through to register.</p></div><div class="bento"><div class="prob prob-1 reveal"><span class="num">01</span><h3>Google can't see you.</h3><p>No schema markup. No SEO content. Page-speed scores in the 30s. Runners searching for “fast fall marathon” land on someone else's race — not yours.</p><div class="rank-viz"><div class="q">“fast fall marathon”</div><div class="results"><div class="result"><span class="pos">#1</span>Competitor Race</div><div class="result"><span class="pos">#2</span>Another Competitor</div><div class="result"><span class="pos">#3</span>Race Calendar Listing</div><div class="result you"><span class="pos">#47</span>Your Race</div></div></div><span class="stat">Top race sites score 95+ on Lighthouse SEO</span></div><div class="prob prob-2 reveal"><span class="num">02</span><h3>It doesn't sell the race.</h3><p>No course story. No elevation profile. No qualifying info. The runner who's almost ready gets a form, not a reason.</p><span class="stat">3 seconds to make the case</span></div><div class="prob prob-3 reveal"><span class="num">03</span><h3>You can't capture the maybes.</h3><p>The runner who came to look but isn't ready to pay? Gone. No email capture, no retargeting.</p><span class="stat">~70% don't register that day</span></div></div></section>
    <section class="templates" id="templates"><div class="section-head reveal"><div><div class="kicker">The templates</div><h2>Five archetypes. Pick the one that fits your race.</h2></div><p class="lead">Each template is engineered to the same standard — perfect Lighthouse scores, full schema markup, mobile-first conversion. Destination Major and Performance foundations are ready; Community, Trail, and Charity follow.</p></div><div class="tpl-grid"><article class="tpl-card reveal"><span class="label">Live demo</span><div class="preview-ocean"><div class="sun"></div><svg class="mt" viewBox="0 0 600 140" preserveAspectRatio="none"><path d="M0 140 L0 100 L80 50 L180 90 L300 35 L420 80 L520 45 L600 75 L600 140Z" fill="#1B2433" opacity=".7"/><path d="M0 140 L0 120 L100 80 L240 115 L380 70 L500 110 L600 90 L600 140Z" fill="#0B0E13"/></svg><div class="copy"><div class="e">● Destination Major</div><h3>Cinematic. Clear.<br/>Built for travelers.</h3></div></div><div class="info"><h4>Destination Major</h4><p>For races runners travel for. Dark cinematic hero, layered ridgelines, sunrise palette.</p></div></article><article class="tpl-card reveal"><span class="label">Live demo</span><div class="preview-performance" aria-label="Performance template marathon homepage preview"><div class="perf-browser"><div class="perf-nav"><span class="perf-brand">Summit City Marathon</span><span>Course</span><span>Qualify</span><span class="perf-nav-cta">Register</span></div><div class="perf-hero"><div class="perf-copy"><div class="e">● Performance marathon</div><h3>Fast. Precise.<br/>Marathon-ready.</h3><p>Flat certified marathon course with clear BQ details.</p></div><div class="perf-clock" aria-hidden="true"><span>42D</span><em>09H</em><small>Start countdown</small></div></div><div class="perf-register"><strong>Marathon registration open</strong><span>BQ course details · certified 26.2</span><b>Register →</b></div><div class="perf-stats"><div><strong>320′</strong><span>Gain</span></div><div><strong>26.2</strong><span>Certified</span></div><div><strong>42</strong><span>Days to start</span></div></div><div class="perf-course"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div></div></div><div class="info"><h4>Performance</h4><p>For fast certified road races. Clock-first structure for marathon qualification, PR goals, countdown urgency, and course-proof messaging.</p></div></article></div><div class="tpl-row-2 stagger"><div class="tpl-mini m1"><div><div class="ttl">Community</div><div class="sub">Coming next</div></div></div><div class="tpl-mini m2"><div><div class="ttl">Trail</div><div class="sub">Coming next</div></div></div><div class="tpl-mini m3"><div><div class="ttl">Charity</div><div class="sub">Coming next</div></div></div></div></section>
    <section class="proof" id="mockups"><div class="section-head reveal"><div><div class="kicker">Private mockup proof</div><h2>See the gap before you buy.</h2></div><p class="lead">For outreach, we can prepare a private, race-specific concept that shows how your current homepage could turn more runner interest into a faster, clearer registration path. Example concept only — not a customer testimonial.</p></div><div class="proof-grid"><article class="proof-card reveal"><span class="label">Before</span><h3>Current race site</h3><p>Generic event details, thin search signals, and a registration link doing all the conversion work.</p><div class="proof-lines"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div></article><article class="proof-card proof-after reveal"><span class="label">Private mockup</span><h3>Ocean Marathon-style concept</h3><p>Course story, elevation cues, registration CTA, SEO structure, and ownership-ready tracking plan in one modern page.</p><div class="mini-browser"><div class="mini-sun"></div><div class="mini-mountain"></div><strong>Ocean Marathon</strong><small>Coastal miles. Clear path to register.</small></div></article></div></section>
    <section class="how" id="how"><div class="section-head reveal"><div><div class="kicker">How it works</div><h2>Four steps. Two weeks. One launch.</h2></div><p class="lead">We've productized everything. No agency back-and-forth, no estimates that drift.</p></div><div class="steps-wrap"><div class="steps-line"></div><div class="steps stagger">{['Pick your template','Complete the intake form','We build & you review','Launch on your domain'].map((t,i)=><div class="step"><div class="step-icon">0{i+1}</div><h3>{t}</h3><p>{['One discovery call. We recommend the template that fits your race archetype.','One form captures everything: course, distances, pricing, sponsors, schedule, FAQs.','Staging URL in days. One revision pass included. Founder reviews everything before it ships.','We wire DNS, you keep ownership. Site lives on your URL with SSL, GA4, schema markup.'][i]}</p><span class="time">{['15 min','20–30 min','7–14 days','~24 hrs'][i]}</span></div>)}</div></div></section>
    <section class="cred" id="why"><div class="cred-inner"><div class="reveal"><div class="kicker">Why us</div><h2>We already serve the race director community.</h2><p>StartLine Sites is built by the team behind <strong>bostonmarathonqualifyingraces.com</strong> — the largest BQ race directory online — to help race directors turn runner interest into registrations.</p><p>We don't replace your registration platform. Your money flow stays where it is. Our job is to help more interested runners get there.</p><p class="signature">From the team behind BMQR</p></div><div class="measure reveal"><h3>What We Measure On Every Site</h3><div class="measure-grid">{[['95+','Lighthouse Performance'],['100','Lighthouse SEO'],['100','Accessibility (WCAG AA)'],['<2s','Largest Contentful Paint'],['<0.1','Cumulative Layout Shift'],['14 days','Contract to Live']].map(([v,l])=><div class="metric"><div class="v">{v}</div><div class="l">{l}</div></div>)}</div></div></div></section>
    <section class="built-for"><div class="built-for-inner reveal"><div class="kicker centered">Who we serve</div><h2>Built for the races runners actually <span class="ital">talk about.</span></h2><div class="bf-grid stagger">{['USATF-Certified Road Races','Boston Qualifiers','Trail & Ultra Events','Community 5Ks & 10Ks','Charity & Fundraising Races','Multi-Distance Weekends','RRCA Member Clubs'].map(c=><span class="bf-chip">{c}</span>)}</div></div></section>
    <section class="pricing" id="pricing"><div class="section-head reveal"><div><div class="kicker">Pricing</div><h2>Start with the package that matches your race.</h2></div><p class="lead">One-time setup plus a monthly maintenance tier. Standard is recommended for most races that want conversion support after launch.</p></div><div class="price-grid">{[{key:'starter',n:'Starter',p:'$1,500',deposit:'$750 deposit',m:'+ $99/mo · Foundation',d:'Smaller races, lean setup',f:['Template + content load','Registration deep-link','Schema markup + Search Console','GA4 + conversion tracking','One revision pass','Hosting on your domain']},{key:'standard',n:'Standard',p:'$2,500',deposit:'$1,250 deposit',m:'+ $249/mo · Growth',d:'Recommended for most mid-size races',featured:true,f:['Everything in Starter','Custom course visualization','Photo gallery','Monthly content updates','Monthly conversion reports','Quarterly SEO audit + fixes']},{key:'premium',n:'Premium',p:'$4,500',deposit:'Proposal required',m:'+ $499/mo · Performance',d:'Larger race weekends needing deeper growth support',proposalOnly:true,f:['Everything in Standard','Color/typography tuning','Copywriting pass','Two revision passes','Retargeting pixel setup','Sponsor logo management']}].map(t=><article class:list={['tier','reveal',{featured:t.featured}]} data-package-card={t.key}>{t.featured&&<span class="tier-tag">Recommended</span>}<h3>{t.n}</h3><div class="desc">{t.d}</div><div class="price"><span class="num">{t.p}</span><span class="per">setup</span></div><span class="monthly">{t.m}</span><span class="deposit">{t.proposalOnly ? 'Audit + proposal before deposit' : `50% to start: ${t.deposit}`}</span><ul>{t.f.map(x=><li>{x}</li>)}</ul><button class:list={['btn',t.featured?'btn-accent':'btn-ghost']} data-scroll="audit" data-package-tier={t.key}>{t.proposalOnly ? 'Request proposal' : `Choose ${t.n}`}</button></article>)}</div><div class="custom-note reveal"><strong>Need help choosing?</strong> Request the audit without picking a package, and we'll recommend the right setup before you pay a deposit.</div></section>
    <section class="audit" id="audit"><div class="audit-inner"><div class="audit-copy reveal"><div class="kicker gold">Private race website audit</div><h2>See the top opportunities hiding in your <span class="ital">current site.</span></h2><p>Send us your race name and current URL. We'll review the page like a runner deciding whether to register and identify the clearest next moves.</p><div class="what-you-get"><div class="what-title">What you'll get back</div><ul>{['Top 3 opportunities to improve registrations','SEO/search visibility gaps','Mobile and speed blockers','Registration funnel friction'].map(x=><li>{x}</li>)}</ul><p class="teaser"><em>We may include additional opportunities and a private mockup concept when there is a clear fit.</em></p></div></div><div class="audit-form-wrap reveal"><div class="report-mock"><div class="rm-head"><span>Private Audit</span><span class="pill">Mockup</span></div><div class="rm-title">Your Race · 2026</div>{[['Top Opportunities','3',''],['SEO','Review','warn'],['Mobile','Review','warn'],['Mockup Fit','Possible','']].map(([a,b,c])=><div class="rm-row"><span>{a}</span><span class:list={['v',c]}>{b}</span></div>)}</div><form class="audit-form" id="auditForm"><h3>Request a private audit</h3><p class="sub">Top-3 opportunities first. Starter and Standard can show a deposit link after submission; Premium requires a proposal first.</p><input id="packageTier" name="packageTier" type="hidden" value="" /><div class="selected-package" id="selectedPackage" hidden>Selected package: <strong id="selectedPackageLabel"></strong></div><div class="field"><label for="raceName">Race name</label><input id="raceName" name="raceName" type="text" placeholder="e.g., Ocean Marathon" required /></div><div class="field"><label for="currentUrl">Your current site or reg URL</label><input id="currentUrl" name="currentUrl" type="url" placeholder="https://..." required /></div><div class="field"><label for="auditName">Your name</label><input id="auditName" name="auditName" type="text" placeholder="First Last" required /></div><div class="field"><label for="auditEmail">Email</label><input id="auditEmail" name="auditEmail" type="email" placeholder="you@email.com" required /></div><div class="field"><label for="notes">Anything we should know? <span class="optional">Optional</span></label><textarea id="notes" name="notes" rows="3" maxlength="1200" placeholder="Race date, registration platform, timeline, or goals"></textarea></div><div class="field hp-field" aria-hidden="true"><label for="companyWebsite">Company website</label><input id="companyWebsite" name="companyWebsite" type="text" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off" /></div><button type="submit" class="btn btn-accent">Request private audit →</button><div class="form-note">We'll review your race site and send back the clearest opportunities. No sales call required.</div><div class="form-msg" id="formMsg" role="status" aria-live="polite"></div></form></div></div></section>
    <section class="faq" id="faq"><div class="faq-wrap"><div class="reveal"><div class="kicker">Good to know</div><h2>Questions, answered.</h2></div><div class="faq-list" id="faqList">{[['Do we have to switch from RunSignup or RaceRoster?','No. We deep-link to your existing registration platform. Your money flow stays exactly where it is.'],['Who owns the domain and the site?','You do. Always. We host the site on your domain — you register and own it.'],['Who owns GA4 and Search Console data?','You do. We configure Google Analytics 4 and Google Search Console tracking, but the Google accounts, properties, access, and data remain under your ownership.'],["What if I don't have logos or photos ready?","Bring what you have. We'll work with low-res versions while better assets get sourced."],['What does the monthly fee actually cover?','Hosting, SSL, uptime monitoring, content updates, reporting, and tier-specific services.'],['Can I see what the analytics look like?','Yes — every customer gets their own Google Analytics 4 property and Search Console setup.'],['What if my race is in a few weeks and I need this fast?','Starter goes live in 7 days if intake and assets are ready on day one.'],['Do you work with non-marathon races?','Yes. Any road race — 5K, 10K, half, marathon, and ultra.']].map(([q,a])=><div class="faq-item"><button class="faq-q" type="button">{q}<span class="pm"></span></button><div class="faq-a"><p>{a}</p></div></div>)}</div></div></section>
    <section class="finale"><h2 class="reveal">Turn runner interest <span class="ital">into registrations.</span></h2><p class="reveal">See where runners are getting stuck, what your current site is missing, and how a faster, clearer race website could move them toward registration.</p><button class="btn btn-accent reveal" data-scroll="audit">Request private audit →</button></section>
  </main><footer><div class="foot"><div><div class="brand footbrand"><img class="brand-mark" src={brandLogoHref} alt="StartLine Sites" width="1200" height="360" /></div><p>Fast, SEO-optimized race websites for race directors — built for search, speed, and signups.</p></div><div><div class="foot-title">Product</div><ul><li><a href="#templates">Templates</a></li><li><a href="#how">How it works</a></li><li><a href="#pricing">Pricing</a></li><li><a href="#audit">Private audit</a></li></ul></div><div><div class="foot-title">Company</div><ul><li><a href="https://bostonmarathonqualifyingraces.com">BMQR</a></li><li><a href="#why">Why us</a></li><li><a href="#faq">FAQ</a></li><li><a href="#mockups">Private mockups</a></li></ul></div><div><div class="foot-title">Connect</div><ul><li><a href="#audit">Contact</a></li><li><a href="#audit">Newsletter</a></li><li><a href="https://bostonmarathonqualifyingraces.com">BMQR</a></li><li><a href="#pricing">For directors</a></li></ul></div></div><div class="foot-bottom"><span>© 2026 StartLine Sites. From the team behind BMQR.</span><span>Built for search, speed, and signups.</span></div></footer>
  <script>
    import '../scripts/nav.ts';
    import '../scripts/smoothScroll.ts';
    import '../scripts/reveal.ts';
    import '../scripts/auditForm.ts';
  </script>
</Base>
<style>
nav{position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;z-index:1000;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:18px clamp(20px,5vw,56px);transition:all .3s ease}nav.scrolled{padding:12px clamp(20px,5vw,56px);background:rgba(250,250,247,.82);backdrop-filter:blur(18px) saturate(140%);box-shadow:0 1px 0 var(--line)}nav.menu-open{z-index:1200;background:var(--paper);box-shadow:0 1px 0 var(--line)}.brand{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;font-family:"Instrument Serif",serif;font-size:1.6rem;letter-spacing:-.01em}.brand-mark{display:block;width:168px;height:auto;flex:0 0 auto}.footbrand .brand-mark{width:150px}.nav-links{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:32px}.nav-links a{font-weight:500;font-size:.92rem;transition:color .2s}.nav-links a:hover{color:var(--accent)}.hamburger{display:none;flex-direction:column;gap:5px;background:none;border:none;padding:10px;min-width:44px;min-height:44px}.hamburger span{display:block;width:24px;height:2px;background:var(--ink);transition:.3s}.hero{position:relative;padding:140px clamp(20px,5vw,56px) 96px;background:var(--paper);overflow:hidden}.hero::before{content:"";position:absolute;top:0;right:-15%;width:60%;height:120%;background:radial-gradient(circle at 30% 40%, rgba(255,77,61,.06), transparent 70%);pointer-events:none}.hero-inner{max-width:var(--maxw);margin:0 auto;display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.15fr 1fr;gap:60px;align-items:center;position:relative;z-index:2}.eyebrow{display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;font-size:.72rem;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--accent);margin-bottom:28px}.eyebrow::before{content:"";width:24px;height:1.5px;background:var(--accent)}.hero h1{font-size:clamp(2.8rem,6.5vw,5.6rem);margin-bottom:24px}.ital{font-style:italic;color:var(--accent)}.hero p.lead{font-size:clamp(1.05rem,1.7vw,1.25rem);color:rgba(14,23,41,.7);max-width:48ch;margin-bottom:36px;line-height:1.55}.hero-cta{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:12px;margin-bottom:38px}.t